g.text: UML Diagram: Class CorrespondenceTable in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― Agent: Actor that performs a role in relation to a process or product.
a.xlink:title: ― Agent: Actor that performs a role in relation to a process or product.

a.title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.
a.xlink:title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.

a.title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.
a.xlink:title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.

a.title: ― ConceptMap: Correspondence between concepts in a correspondence table.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptMap: Correspondence between concepts in a correspondence table.

a.title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.
a.xlink:title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.

a.title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.
a.xlink:title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: ― DateRange: Expresses a date/time range using a start date and end date (both with the structure of Date and supporting the use of ISO and non-ISO date structures). Use in all locations where a range of dates is required, i.e. validFor, embargoPeriod, collectionPeriod, etc.
a.xlink:title: ― DateRange: Expresses a date/time range using a start date and end date (both with the structure of Date and supporting the use of ISO and non-ISO date structures). Use in all locations where a range of dates is required, i.e. validFor, embargoPeriod, collectionPeriod, etc.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― hasContact: The person(s) who may be contacted for additional information about the correspondence table. Can be an individual or organization.
a.xlink:title: ― hasContact: The person(s) who may be contacted for additional information about the correspondence table. Can be an individual or organization.

a.title: ― isMaintainedBy: The unit or group of persons who are responsible for the correspondence table (i.e., for maintaining and updating it).
a.xlink:title: ― isMaintainedBy: The unit or group of persons who are responsible for the correspondence table (i.e., for maintaining and updating it).

a.title: ― isOwnedBy: The statistical office, other authority or section that created and maintains the correspondence table. A correspondence table may have several owners.
a.xlink:title: ― isOwnedBy: The statistical office, other authority or section that created and maintains the correspondence table. A correspondence table may have several owners.

a.title: ― has: Correspondence table has zero to many concept maps.
a.xlink:title: ― has: Correspondence table has zero to many concept maps.

a.title: ― hasSource: Level from which the correspondence is made. Correspondences might be restricted to a specified level in the node set. In this case, target items are assigned only to source items on the given level. If no level is indicated, source items can be assigned to any level of the target node set.
a.xlink:title: ― hasSource: Level from which the correspondence is made. Correspondences might be restricted to a specified level in the node set. In this case, target items are assigned only to source items on the given level. If no level is indicated, source items can be assigned to any level of the target node set.

a.title: ― hasTarget: Level to which the correspondence is made. Correspondences might be restricted to a specified Level in the node set. In this case, target items are assigned only to source items on the given level. If no level is indicated, target items can be assigned to any level of the source node set.
a.xlink:title: ― hasTarget: Level to which the correspondence is made. Correspondences might be restricted to a specified Level in the node set. In this case, target items are assigned only to source items on the given level. If no level is indicated, target items can be assigned to any level of the source node set.

a.title: ― mapsTo: The statistical classification(s) from which the correspondence is made.
a.xlink:title: ― mapsTo: The statistical classification(s) from which the correspondence is made.
